SIMPLE: penetrate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Penetrate
<hw>Pen"e*trate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Penetrated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Penetrating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>penetratus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>penetrare</ets> to penetrate; akin
to <ets>penitus</ets> inward, inwardly, and perh. to <ets>pens</ets>
with, in the power of, <ets>penus</ets> store of food, innermost part of
a temple.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To enter into; to make way into the
interior of; to effect an entrance into; to pierce; <as>as, light
<ex>penetrates</ex> darkness</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To affect profoundly through the senses or feelings;
to touch with feeling; to make sensible; to move deeply; <as>as, to
<ex>penetrate</ex> one's heart with pity</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The translator of Homer should <qex>penetrate</qex> himself with a
sense of the plainness and directness of Homer's style.</q> <rj><qau>M.
Arnold.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To pierce into by the mind; to arrive at the inner
contents or meaning of, as of a mysterious or difficult subject; to
comprehend; to understand.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Things which here were too subtile for us to
<qex>penetrate</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Ray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Penetrate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Penetrate
<hw>Pen"e*trate</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To pass; to make way; to
pierce. Also used figuratively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Preparing to <qex>penetrate</qex> to the north and west.</q>
<rj><qau>J. R. Green.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Born where Heaven's influence scarce can <qex>penetrate</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sweet of life that <qex>penetrates</qex> so near.</q>
<rj><qau>Daniel.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Penetrating</ent>⟦br⟧
